CSS

Rules made up of Selectors
Semicolon-Separated list of Declarations
Declarations made up of a Property-Value Pair

div.bold-text {
	font-weight: 700;
}

div.bold-text (<-Selector) {
	font-weight: (<-Property) 700; (<-Value)
}

Universal selector = *

* {
     color: purple;
}

Type Selector

div {
  color: white;
}

Class Selector

<div class="alert-text">Please agree to our terms of service.</div>

.alert-text {
  color: red;
}

Id Selector

<div id="title">My Awesome 90's Page</div>

#title {
  background-color: red;
}

Grouping Selector
two groups of elements sharing style declarations, declare them together instead of redundant text

.read,
.unread {
  color: white;
  background-color: black;
}

Chaining Selectors
chaining both .subsection and .header

.subsection.header {
  color: red;
}

Works with ID as well

.subsection#preview {
  color: blue;
}


